On behalf of Little Droid Tech (My startup Company), I am happy to provide you an intriguing
mobile app proposal to the University which will be used by students. The App name is QUON.
A mobile platform for students in accessing notes and Questions. More of the design is discussed
in the Project Overview.
Little Droid Tech is a provider of mobile apps specializing in innovative and cost-effective

INTRODUCTION
Little Droid Tech, QUON Proposal 2019.
PROJECT OVERVIEW;
This project has provided a Mobile App engineered to provide a dynamic and engaging
experience for mobile users. The App will enable its users to easily access their class notes, also,
students will also be able to access a wide variety of questions from past papers at the palm of
their hands. The App has also been integrated for students to be able to access their missing
mark forms online without going to the Admin. There is also a section of events for users to get
updates of events happening around the University.
We have integrated the App with the Firebase Database so that we can give our users real-time
Data and be able to authenticate students while logging in. Firebase will also help us on the
Analytics side of it, and has the capabilities of sending users notifications direct to their mobile
devices.
OBJECTIVES;
Q-UON mobile app for University of Nairobi School of Business has the following features,
 Create an Android compatible Application which, once downloaded onto your student's
phone, will
 Easy accessibility of Notes and Past-Papers
 Provide a convenient Missing mark platform for students to be able to
submit their missing marks online (For those who have missing mark)
 Increase Communications with your students through dynamic updatable
Information functions.
 Events happening around the school will be updated also in the Event
section of the App.
 Increase Social Marketing opportunities through “Tell My Friend”
Function in the App which post to Social Media Platforms.
PROJECT OVERVIEW, OBJECTIVES AND SCOPE.
Little Droid Tech, QUON Proposal 2019.
The scope of design option to include:
 Full design using existing brand and color (University’s Custom Color) i.e. Blue and
White.
 Notes Activity page for students to access their notes. (Pocket Notes)
 Question page for accessing past papers of the previous years.
 Events page, where events will be posted online on the App, this will ease
communication when communicating about events.
 Missing mark section will allow students to submit their complaints online effectively.
- On correction of the missing mark, the user will also be updated via the App.
